{"TopicId":200046,"ForumId":70,"TopicTitle":"Rotate the Mun","CreatedByName":"Sarxis","CreatedById":130923,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-03T07:12:41Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Sarxis","CreatedById":130923,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-03T07:12:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to switch the facing of the Mun.\u00A0 It\u0027s always bothered me that the Farside Crater faces the Mun\u0027s prograde orientation instead of, you know, actually facing the farside (Eastside Crater too for that matter).\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I am wondering if it\u0027s possible to delve into the game\u0027s core files and manipulate them easily just to turn the Mun 90\u00B0 to\u00A0rectify this IMMENSE and SERIOUSLY IMPORTANT issue.\u00A0 \u00A0 \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for any info!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-02-03T07:19:48Z\u0022 title=\u002202/03/2021 07:19  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 3, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Sarxis\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-03T07:44:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not possible without Kopernicus. With Kopernicus it\u0027s pretty easy. Once you learn Kopernicus \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/kerbal-forum-uploads/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EPick your poison depending on your version:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022200868\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3923162574\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/195699-181-111r-t-bs-kopernicus-unified-bleeding-edge-branch/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:195px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022200888\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1434942992\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/194936-181-191-kopernicus-continued/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:195px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sarxis","CreatedById":130923,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-03T07:47:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do have Kopernicus!\u00A0 I also didn\u0027t think about Hyperedit (mostly because I\u0027ve never personally used Hyperedit.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I was curious if it\u0027s possible to change the game files by hand directly, because hacking my core game files is my preferred way of destroying my KSP installation \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-03T10:08:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223919306\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022200046\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221612338422\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130923\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sarxis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Sarxis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I was curious if it\u0027s possible to change the game files by hand directly\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not. Planet definitions aren\u0027t in any of the configs, sadly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sarxis","CreatedById":130923,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-03T11:57:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s alright - just ended up using Hyperedit to change the Mun\u0027s initial rotation orientation from 230\u00B0 to 150\u00B0,\u00A0 which put the Farside Crater on the... far side.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for your help!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-03T12:09:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223919374\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022200046\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221612353461\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130923\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sarxis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, Sarxis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s alright - just ended up using Hyperedit to change the Mun\u0027s initial rotation orientation from 230\u00B0 to 150\u00B0,\u00A0 which put the Farside Crater on the... far side.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for your help!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo problem. I\u0027m not 100% sure but I *think* you have to make that change every time you load the game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sarxis","CreatedById":130923,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-03T12:11:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a way in Hyperedit to save the changes to a file which loads every time you start KSP.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.kerbaltek.com/hyperedit\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EHyperEdit - Kerbaltek\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Can I save the positions of planets after changing them with Planet Editor?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdl\u003E\u003Cdd style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;border-color:#000000;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;color:#000000;font-size:20px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nYes! Version 1.3 saves your changes to a file and then reloads them on startup.\u0022\n\u003C/dd\u003E\n\u003C/dl\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rambow_Ninja94","CreatedById":210641,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-05T18:42:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI believe hyper edit can do this as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002234556\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1578858024\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/34785-111-hyperedit-v158-july-10-2018-cheat-teleporter-orbitplanet-editor-more/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:195px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003EOOPS didn\u0027t\u00A0see the above comment\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-04-05T18:43:55Z\u0022 title=\u002204/05/2021 06:43  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EApril 5, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Rambow_Ninja94\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Edidn\u0026#039;t read the above comment\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}